==English==

===Etymology===
An abbreviation of Yagi-Uda antenna. Named after two Japanese engineers Shintaro Uda and Hidetsugu Yagi.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} A directional antenna consisting of two or more dipoles in the same plane with all dipoles parallel to each other.

